## GOVERNANCE RULES

### MUST DO
- Every flow definition MUST exist as versioned JSON in `flows/definitions/`
- Every flow MUST have a `metadata.yaml` entry with: owner, version, domain, testCoverage, costPerRun
- All flow executions MUST be logged to `prisma.aiSession`
- Healthcare domain flows MUST trigger `createAuditLog()` for HIPAA compliance
- Shadow mode MUST be enabled for any flow version upgrade (`minAgreementRate: 0.90`)
- Cost limiter MUST be checked before every flow execution

### MUST NOT
- Never expose Langflow port publicly — proxy all requests via Orchestrator
- Never deploy flows without passing quality gates (>95% Promptfoo, >0.85 Ragas)
- Never skip session logging, even on error paths
- Never run Langflow version < 1.3.0 (RCE vulnerability CVE-2025-3248)
- Never bypass shadow mode rollback when agreement rate < 90%

### SLAs
- Orchestrator API latency: < 500ms (p99, excluding LLM time)
- API uptime: 99.9%
- Dashboard load time: < 3 seconds
- Canary rollback trigger: within 5 minutes of degradation
- Flow sync to Git: every 6 hours (cron)

